
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `dbus-uuidgen` baraye dorost kardane yek UUID (Universally Unique Identifier) jadid baraye estefade dar DBus (Desktop Bus) be kar miravad. UUID yek code unique ast ke baraye shenasayi kardane service-ha va object-ha dar DBus estefade mishavad.  

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `dbus-uuidgen` --> 🗝️ Dorost kardane yek UUID jadid va chap kardane aan dar terminal.
    🔹 `dbus-uuidgen --ensure` --> 🔒 Agar file UUID mojood nabashad, yek file jadid misazad va UUID ra dar aan zakhire mikonad. Agar mojood bashad, UUID ra az file mikhanad.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ dbus-uuidgen

    🔹 UUID jadid dorost mikonad va chap mikonad.

    $ dbus-uuidgen --ensure

    🔹 Motmaen mishavad ke yek file UUID vojood darad va UUID ra az aan mikhanad ya dar aan zakhire mikonad.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ dbus-uuidgen > my_uuid.txt

    🔹 Yek UUID jadid dorost mikonad va aan ra dar yek file be name `my_uuid.txt` zakhire mikonad.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `dbus-uuidgen` command is used to generate a new UUID (Universally Unique Identifier) for use with D-Bus (Desktop Bus). A UUID is a unique code used to identify services and objects in D-Bus.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `dbus-uuidgen` --> 🗝️ Generate a new UUID and print it to the terminal.
    🔹 `dbus-uuidgen --ensure` --> 🔒 If a UUID file doesn't exist, create a new file and store the UUID in it. If it exists, read the UUID from the file.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ dbus-uuidgen

    🔹 Generates and prints a new UUID.

    $ dbus-uuidgen --ensure

    🔹 Ensures that a UUID file exists and either reads the UUID from it or stores a new one in it.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ dbus-uuidgen > my_uuid.txt

    🔹 Generates a new UUID and stores it in a file named `my_uuid.txt`.

